# Agent Smart Account Rule

- Do not use Privy built-in smart accounts for this project.
- Use Privy only as the user's EOA wallet/auth source.
- The smart account used for auth, delegation, and session packaging must be the MetaMask-based smart account associated with the registered gym agent.
- Treat agent registration and delegation/session-package bootstrap as separate flows.
- If the registered agent exists but delegation/session state is missing, do not redirect to registration. Fail explicitly or start the delegation bootstrap flow.
- When validating auth, target the registered agent smart account and its associated owner EOA, not a Privy smart account abstraction.
